<br>
     What I'd like to know is: what stats other than intelligence should be focused upon for him ..hp/mana?  sta? dex? I understand that dex affects cast throughs?  And how important is it to have high INT at lvl 40?<br>
<br>
Also what are the spells that I need to keep memmed when I am in a group with him?  (I'm sure the mez and charm, haste and root spells, but what else?)  In group should I have a pet up too?  <br>
<br>
     I'm not totally ignorant to the class as my main is a ranger and Chanters are one of my favorite classes to pair up with, and I always see that the enchanter of our group is taken care of.<br>
<br>
     And if I use him in a group I don't want to be the cause of a whipe, so any help you could give in the way of developing this character and strategy would be appreciated. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rangerlahru>Ranger Lahru</A> at: 4/2/03 11:18:08 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=charmroxors>Charmroxors</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#330000>(4/2/03 1:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=68.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: suggestions/advice requested</span><hr size=1> int affects your manapool, the higher your int, the bigger your total manapool will be. this is your main stat to try and upgrade. after that i'd go for sta, the more hitpoints you have, the better your chances at staying alive are. dex makes it so casts have a less chance of being interuppted (if you move or whatnot during the cast) but its not something i'd worry about too much. the other stat i would try to keep up is your charisma, it affects the length of your charm spells. get a pair of opal encrusted steins and equip when charming, +50 cha always helps =)<br>
<br>
depending on what you're doing will affect your spell slots... but i always have an ae stun loaded (very fast casting time) and a mez loaded. the only time my nuke is really loaded is during a raid where adds arent a problem. my spell lineup usually goes as this - 1. kei 2. haste/rune 3. slow 4. ae stun 5. single mez 6. root 7. tash 8. charm .. thats just my lineup for solo'ing / duo'ing. during group situations i'd have an ae-mez loaded and a low resist low length mez loaded.<br>
<br>
[the animation] pets cost too much damn mana to worry about in a group... <br>
<br>
take the chanter to somewhere that you could bow kite with your ranger at that level, and practice charm solo'ing... with enough practice you will be surprised with what you can do.<br>
<br>
